tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE car_warranty_info (
    manufacturer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    manufacturer_name VARCHAR(255),
    warranty_duration INT,
    expiration_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE Cars (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    car_model VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    manufacturer_id INT NOT NULL,
    production_year INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (manufacturer_id) REFERENCES CarManufacturers(id)
);

CREATE TABLE Manufacturers ( manufacturer_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 manufacturer_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
 manufacturer_country VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL );

CREATE TABLE CarModels ( model_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 model_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
 manufacturer_id INT NOT NULL,
 production_year INT NOT NULL,
 warranty_years INT NOT NULL,
 expiration_date DATE );

CREATE TABLE WarrantyInfo ( warranty_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
 model_id INT NOT NULL,
 expiration_date DATE );

CREATE TABLE Warranty (
	warranty_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	warranty_length INT NOT NULL,
	expiration_date DATE,
	model_id INT,
	FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES CarModel(model_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Customer (
	customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	customer_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
	purchase_date DATE,
	model_id INT,
	warranty_id INT,
	FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES CarModel(model_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (warranty_id) REFERENCES Warranty(warranty_id)
);

CREATE TABLE car_manufacturers (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  name STRING,
  location STRING
)

CREATE TABLE car_models (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  manufacturer_id UUID,
  model_name STRING
)

CREATE TABLE warranties (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  car_model_id UUID,
  start_date DATE,
  expiration_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE warranty_issues (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  warranty_id UUID,
  issue_description STRING
)

CREATE TABLE warranty_history (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  warranty_id UUID,
  event_date DATE,
  event_description STRING
)
